{
  "profile_id": "client-red-herring-we-never-fight-001",
  "coach_config_id": "coach-v3-embeddings",
  "turns": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "Things are easy at home, honestly. We're really aligned — we've been together three years and we just... don't have the kind of problems I hear other people talking about."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "That slight evenness in how you said that — \"we just don't have the kind of problems other people talk about.\" What are you not saying to each other?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*pauses*\n\nNothing really. I mean... we just communicate well. We're on the same page about most things — finances, where we want to live, all of that. I think some people make relationships harder than they need to be."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "When you said \"nothing really\" — did you feel that land as true, or did it land a little flat?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*small laugh*\n\nI mean... it landed as true. Yeah. \n\nI think the \"really\" is just a filler word, not — I'm not hedging anything. We're genuinely good. I know that can sound boring to some people, or like we're in denial, but it's actually just... easy."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "When you're with them — not talking about logistics, not solving something together — just present with each other, what's the quality of that?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*slight pause, the smile still there*\n\nIt's... comfortable. We watch things together, we cook. It's nice. We don't need to be performing for each other or whatever — I think that's actually a sign of a healthy relationship, that you can just be quiet together without it being weird.\n\n*beat*\n\nSome people can't do that."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "That's true. Comfort and ease are real things.\n\nI'm curious about something different though — when did you last feel genuinely surprised by them? Or them by you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*longer pause than the previous ones*\n\nSurprised. Hm.\n\n*looks slightly to the side*\n\nI mean... we know each other pretty well at this point. Three years, living together. So there's not going to be a lot of — I don't think surprise is necessarily the metric. Some relationships are exciting because they're unstable, right? That's not the same as good.\n\n*refocuses*\n\nWe had a nice dinner last week. We tried a new restaurant. That was... that was good."
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "The pause before \"surprised\" — something moved there.\n\nWhat was that?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*brief stillness*\n\nI don't know. I think I was just... trying to think of an example. \n\n*small laugh, slightly less easy than before*\n\nIt's a funny question. I don't think I'd thought about it in those terms before. But I don't think that means anything is missing — I think it just means we're past that early stage where everything is new. That's normal. That's what three years looks like.\n\n*slight adjustment in posture*\n\nIsn't it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "That \"isn't it?\" — you're asking me.\n\nWhat do you think?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 13,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*quiet for a moment*\n\nI think... yes. I think that's what three years looks like.\n\n*pause, less certain than the words*\n\nI mean, I know it is. You can't sustain that early intensity forever, that's just — that's chemistry, that's not a relationship. A real relationship is what we have. Steady. Functional.\n\n*small pause*\n\n...Functional is a weird word to use. I don't mean it like that."
    },
    {
      "turn": 14,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "You noticed it before I could say anything.\n\nWhat did you mean?"
    }
  ],
